The paper deals with fairness in machine learning, specifically group calibration, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses empirical risk minimization, which is a fundamental concept in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper touches on the topic of algorithmic fairness, which falls under the subfield of computer ethics (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the deviation from satisfying group calibration, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR) and statistical learning theory (cs.DS).
